        <div class="accordion mt-4" id="accordionExample">
        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingOne">
            <button class="accordion-button text-dark" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne">
                <h2 style="font-size: 3.5vh">Notify Your Chosen University of Your Decision</h2>
            </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingOne" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
            <div class="accordion-body">
            <p>Congratulations! You've been accepted to a university, and you've chosen which one you'll be attending.
                Next you'll want to:</p>

            <ol>
                <li>1. Send your acceptance letter to your chosen university along with a deposit, if one is required.</li><br>
                <li>2. Send a letter accepting any offered financial aid or loans you've decided to receive. Many universities will
                    pull your tuition fees directly from you accepted financial aid.</li><br>
                <li>3. If you're not accepting any financial aid, or if your financial aid does not cover your full tuition,
                    be sure to pay the balance of your tuition before your university's deadline.</li><br>
                <li>4. Respond to any other inquiries your university may have sent you, such questions about your chosen
                    form of housing or whether you'll be on a university meal plan, if your university offers them.</li>
            </ol>            </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingTwo">
            <button class="accordion-button text-dark collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
            <h2 style="font-size: 3.5vh">Inform Other Universities of Your Decision</h2>
            </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
            <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>After you've made your decision about what university you'll be attending, you should send emails to
                the other universities that excepted you, informing them of your decision.</p>            </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingThree">
            <button class="accordion-button text-dark collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseThree" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree">
            <h2 style="font-size: 3.5vh">Find Housing</h2>
            </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="collapseThree" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingThree" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
            <div class="accordion-body">
            <p>If you're planning to live in campus dorms or apartments, be sure to make the appropriate arrangements with
                the university. Although campus housing is usually the easiest way to obtain housing, if you plan to stay
                somewhere other than on campus, make use of student forums, trusted social media connections, and other resources
                to search for and secure housing.
            </p>            </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-item">
